<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="639" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Second Assistant Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Consul <persName type="to">Proffit</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-03-16"><hi rend="italic">March 16,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 47.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 68, of January 28 last, in regard to the refusal of the
                            British authorities to pay the bonds, issued by the Boer government,
                            which are now held by Dr. William H. McGreevy.</p>
                        <p>You will please forward to the department a copy of the decision of the
                            commission by which payment was denied.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>